  "text": "Analysis of the migration from legacy Kafka ConsumerConnector API to new KafkaConsumer API across the three target repositories.\n\n## Legacy ConsumerConnector Interface\n\nThe legacy kafka.consumer.ConsumerConnector (and its Java wrapper kafka.javaapi.consumer.ConsumerConnector) was the old high-level consumer API that stored offsets in ZooKeeper and used blocking KafkaStream message queues. This interface has been completely removed from Kafka and is NOT present in any of the three target repos (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489, sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc, sg-evals/camel--1006f047).\n\n## New KafkaConsumer API Files\n\n### sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\n\n1. clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer.java\n   The primary public-facing new KafkaConsumer class (public class KafkaConsumer<K, V> implements Consumer<K, V>). Uses a delegate pattern, delegating to either ClassicKafkaConsumer or AsyncKafkaConsumer based on group.protocol configuration. This is the replacement for the old ConsumerConnector API.\n\n2. clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ClassicKafkaConsumer.java\n   public class ClassicKafkaConsumer<K, V> implements ConsumerDelegate<K, V>. Implements the classic (pre-KIP-848) group protocol for backward compatibility. Network I/O happens in the application thread. Documented as existing \"for backward compatibility to allow users to continue to use the classic group protocol (pre-KIP 848).\" This is the closest analog to how the old ConsumerConnector operated.\n\n3. clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AsyncKafkaConsumer.java\n   public class AsyncKafkaConsumer<K, V> implements ConsumerDelegate<K, V>. Implements the new KIP-848 next-generation consumer group protocol with a dedicated background network thread and event-driven architecture.\n\n4. clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerDelegate.java\n   Interface that both ClassicKafkaConsumer and AsyncKafkaConsumer implement.\n\n5. clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerDelegateCreator.java\n   Factory that selects between ClassicKafkaConsumer and AsyncKafkaConsumer based on group.protocol config.\n\n6. clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/Consumer.java\n   The Consumer interface defining the full new API contract (commitSync, commitAsync, poll, subscribe, etc.).\n\n### sg-evals/camel--1006f047\n\n7. components/camel-kafka/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/kafka/KafkaConsumer.java\n   Camel's Kafka consumer component (public class KafkaConsumer extends DefaultConsumer). Uses the new org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer.KafkaConsumer API internally to consume from Kafka topics within a Camel route.\n\n8. components/camel-kafka/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/kafka/KafkaFetchRecords.java\n   The actual polling loop that manages org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer.Consumer lifecycle, commit management, and error handling.\n\n## Key Behavioral Differences in Offset Management\n\n### Old ConsumerConnector (historical)\n- Offsets stored in ZooKeeper under /consumers/<group>/offsets/<topic>/<partition>\n- commitOffsets() method for synchronous commit to ZooKeeper\n- Automatic periodic commit via a background ZooKeeper writer\n- Subscription via createMessageStreams() returning blocking KafkaStream iterators\n- No explicit poll() - consumers blocked on iterator.next()\n\n### New KafkaConsumer API (ClassicKafkaConsumer / AsyncKafkaConsumer)\n- Offsets stored in Kafka itself in the internal __consumer_offsets topic\n- commitSync() / commitAsync(OffsetCommitCallback) with explicit, per-partition granularity\n- Automatic commit via enable.auto.commit=true with auto.commit.interval.ms; commits triggered only inside poll() calls\n- subscribe(Collection<String>) + poll(Duration) loop returning ConsumerRecords<K, V>\n- Committed offset = offset of next record to read (last consumed offset + 1)\n- ClassicKafkaConsumer: all I/O (heartbeats, offset commits, fetching) happens synchronously in the calling thread during poll()\n- AsyncKafkaConsumer: heartbeats and network I/O occur on a dedicated background thread; offset commit events are queued as SyncCommitEvent/AsyncCommitEvent objects processed asynchronously\n\nThe flink--0cc95fcc repo does not contain a Kafka connector and has no Kafka consumer implementations relevant to this migration."
